[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Java annotations**\n\nI’m considering how to handle annotations in Java. The `getAnnotations` method returns all public annotations, but private annotations can’t be used directly, as Java doesn't allow private annotation types. However, nested private interfaces can work! I think `Class.getAnnotations` accesses annotations regardless of visibility, which could be problematic for proxies. Using public nested static interfaces is better to avoid access issues. Ultimately, focusing on “active class only” could guide how I use the factory for annotation validation.\n\n**Clarifying annotation validation**\n\nI’m thinking about the call site in `createAnnotationValidator`. The public factory API uses the `ValidateWith` annotation to create an instance. To retrieve the annotation instance, I should consider using the meta annotation. Although I may use `Class.getAnnotation` for reflection, it seems necessary for the public API. I wonder if there's a way to streamline this without going through the normal API, but the factory itself remains public, which is a good option.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_062dbdd24b61d44a016a1048d33300819287712d5ff99a6ef7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEEjkLeiG2HKz2CLezA6R3QwDPH0drxrowq5XlBScXXB9nQwkNRYq2q7zB1TUhHky0fODBjnDYorsDwxhrP8sfsJFYG--Ua_ergw57p54dReLxuFxpDTR-N8gytW9aqIekzNs-_oJHzm_sFo1o2cWwAkC7152KXS02uYfUDtZXczjddBMB5UctoEjaLKqeddrA1-un1TaQZg5c0lZb19IJrTtsxt6i0HKT01v-NeH6UqiO2QoSoSkkB2v6Yn0cC5QMek4riVO5uFQwWyvwKW7JoFWbrjgItfhCHuM6leK2XvSOmVqJKgNqCKECbKPhsM1Dl0XBdcg-RgdRHLNanHvoFR6OIapj0iCkLRA861S6Emj_y1QR3Vvl-4aa6_FD_6mTDeEQOrf7XUL601VdMNv_UK34xxF0tLl0ekhK1tUyRVa_4FIuP2DbKdCnxGt4sGRQFFc3vP_S0O6oY06bYtsFrEP22eMRQSS56zxJut-odDiGBJH4irf63Lgm8ggBGsRRkgitF8SLrrQ_gryHKs8GDBNg4MS_oJhwhxGWQ5a1GInG9DYf_N0iiDalUhi8OGKZncGH8z4zc8dzVTLJJOhfccjxeQdFgaYrjBHxtRbBMRKc4KINvCR3l1L9U_gPlfRRZwmtgI7x3h3h